  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multisectoral Humanitarian Assistance for Displaced and Mobile Populations in the Darfur States, West Kordofan, South Kordofan, and Abyei (PCA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project ensures that affected populations in target communities have improved and equitable access to water sanitation and hygiene services through improved access to safe water, improved access to sanitation services and ensure communities have increased knowledge on safe hygiene as well as delivering emergency services and non-food item assistance to 5,500 of the most vulnerable households. The project is improving nutritional and health status among the most vulnerable populations (particularly children and pregnant and lactating women) in target communities through improved access to efficient nutrition and improved knowledge on nutrition among households and community health workers and other relevant stakeholders. Lastly, livelihood interventions are delivered to tackle food insecurity and malnutrition through agricultural and non-agricultural income generating activities</narrative>
  </description>
